                    "company": "DAF Trucks NV",
                    "description": "The Control Purchasing department within DAF is responsible for the periodic financial reports for the management of PACCAR Purchasing Europe. The department takes care of the monthly financial closing and forecasting. This consists of cost movements reporting such as purchasing savings, chip shortages and raw materials impacts, including coordination with PACCAR entities in Brazil, US and the UK.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\u2022 Monthly closure, including accompanying financial reports of cost movements for purchasing savings, raw materials impacts and chip shortages.\n\u2022 Coordinating Purchasing budget and forecast cycles in coordination and discussion with the business.\n\u2022 Providing accurate, relevant and meaningful ad-hoc analysis to management to support strategic and tactical decision-making.\n\u2022 Monitoring and managing the Internal (Control) processes within the Purchasing Department.\n\u2022 Monitoring and improving the relevant procedures and systems.\n\nReporting to the DAF Purchasing Controller.",
